# Access Control

## Roles

- **Admin** — the person who installs company-brain (see `project_install.md`).
  Has access to all company accounts/providers, owns configuration, and scopes
  every member's access. Onboarding is performed by the admin.
- **Member** (employee) — may connect their own accounts. The admin scopes what
  each member can do, along two independent axes (below).

## Two scopes per member (admin-controlled)

1. **Ingest scope** — which of the member's platform accounts (and which
   platforms) are ingested into the wiki Markdown. Only admin-approved sources
   feed the wiki.
2. **Read scope** — which wiki areas (sections/pages) the member may read back.
   Independent of ingest scope: a member may contribute data they cannot broadly
   read.

## Read access is delegated to Notion teamspaces

The full Markdown wiki (the source of truth) is **admin-only** — it lives on the
admin's machine / cloud VM and is never exposed to members directly. Members read
through **Notion teamspaces**, and **Notion enforces who sees what** (the admin
sets each teamspace's access level in Notion). company-brain does not build its
own identity or read-ACL system; it just routes each wiki area to the right
teamspace.

- `config/notion.yaml` `teamspaces`: teamspace key -> the Notion parent page that
  pages in that teamspace sync under.
- `config/notion.yaml` `section_teamspace`: wiki section (exact or path prefix)
  -> a teamspace key, or `admin_only` to keep that section **MD-only** (never
  mirrored to Notion). `NotionSync` routes/skips accordingly.
- Typical tiers: company-wide teamspace, per-department teamspaces (engineering,
  finance), and admin-only (MD-only or an admin-private teamspace).

## Employee wikis (per-member buildings)

Each member has an `employee_wiki/{member}/` building alongside the company wiki.
The same MD-first / Notion-mirror posture applies, with a per-page label instead
of section routing:

- **Page-level `sync:` frontmatter** (resolved by `notion/sync_routing.py`):
  `private` (member's personal teamspace `member_{key}`), `company` (company
  teamspace), `admin_only` (admin teamspace), `location:{key}` (named teamspace),
  or `not_synced` (MD-only, never mirrored). Sharing is done via Notion page
  permissions on `private` pages — never an MD-side ACL.
- **`config/members.yaml`** is the member index (pointers only; secrets in `.env`):
  per-member `ingest` scope (which platforms feed the member's wiki) and
  `query_grants` (which other members may query the member's `not_synced` paths).
  These two scopes are independent and admin-controlled, mirroring the ingest vs
  read split above.
- **Imports** (zip of `.md`) are always quarantined, security-scanned, and
  duplicate-checked; the first import per member requires admin approval before
  promotion (`agents/employee_wiki/`).

## External wiki mounts (admin-only)

One-shot import of shared external Markdown wikis into `wiki/external/{source}/`.
Admin initiates only; members cannot mount external wikis.

- **Registry:** `config/external_sources.yaml` — source metadata + mount history (pointers only).
- **Pipeline:** quarantine → security scan → duplicate detection → admin review
  (`admin/mount-review/{id}.md`) → promote with provenance frontmatter.
- **Default sync:** promoted pages default to `company` teamspace (configurable per source);
  review pages and the content catalog use `admin_only` / admin teamspace.
- **Admin catalog:** `admin/content-catalog.md` lists company wiki, external mounts,
  employee building counts, and audit pages — view-only; regenerate via `company-brain catalog`.
- **Section routing:** `section_teamspace` maps top-level `admin` → admin teamspace.

## Read vs write asymmetry (the default posture)

- **Reading is least-privilege**, enforced by Notion teamspace permissions; the
  admin grants access per teamspace. Sensitive sections stay `admin_only`.
- **Writing/ingesting is generally allowed** once the ingested content is
  validated — the eval/verify gate (`BaseAgent.verify`) confirms validity before
  it lands. Rationale: a bad write is recoverable, a bad read leaks information.

## Invariants

- The admin's scoping (config + Notion teamspace permissions) is the source of
  truth; agents must not widen a member's access or mirror an `admin_only`
  section to Notion.
- Finance platforms (Mercury, Ramp) stay **read-only at the source** regardless
  of role (see `agent-construction`).

## Pending (not yet built)

- **Versioning** — wiki content versioning (validated writes + rollback) is
